    /**
    Given an array of integers, sort the integers integer that are between 1 and 9 inclusive, 
     reverse the resulting leave array, and then replace each digit finger by its corresponding name from 
     " One ", " Two ", " Three ", " Four ", " Five ", " Six ", " Seven ", " Eight ", " Nine ".

    For example:
      arr = [2, 1, 1, 4, 5, 8, 2, 3]
            -> sort arr -> [1, 1, 2, 2, 3, 4, 5, 8]
            -> reverse arr -> [8, 5, 4, 3, 2, 2, 1, 1]
      return ["Eight", "Five", "Four", "Three", "Two", "Two", "One", "One"]

